&lt;p&gt;Regarding the comma. We keep it as is. Nobody ever uses comma in their emails. In fact even not the pipe character.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12952842" author="tide08" created="Fri, 16 Oct 2009 22:24:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks! I agree that having comma or pipe in email is pretty rare. But comma or semi-colon can be part of name. But we can put some validation on our side.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
